!! Phrase encoding

Phrases encode the 122 ''variable'' bits of the UUID (48 timestamp + 12 rand_a + 62 rand_b), skipping 6 fixed bits (4 version + 2 variant). Padded to 128 bits with 6 trailing zeros → 8 triplets of 16 bits each. Triplet 8's verb (5 bits) and noun's LSB (1 bit) are padding zeros.

